{"key":"processedPost-13452636","value":{"id":13452636,"first":13452162,"last":13543533,"when":1289229233,"utime":"11/08/10 05:13 PM","content":"You want to pasteurize a casing mix, not sterilize.&nbsp; This <i>prevents</i> molds from getting a foothold.<br /><br />Don't skip the lime.&nbsp; If you do, the uncolonized parts of the casing mix are much more easily contaminated.&nbsp; The best place to get hydrated lime is at a feed store, not a nursery.&nbsp; You'll also want to pick up a bag of gypsum there as well.&nbsp; Use gypsum at about 5% to the amount of your casing material.<br />RR","title":"Re: Lime for casing ?"}}